  Bonus Video: Swapping Faces in Video

In this video, I'll show you how to pull off one of the most important AI workflows for filmmakers. We'll discover how to do face swapping in video (deepfakes) in a realistic way. This technology is revolutionary for helping to create character consistency. It can be combined with AI video tools like Runway or Pika Labs to improve your quality.

  • Download the Assets
  • Link to Akool

Workflow for AI Videos with Stable Character Faces:

  • Create Character Image in Midjourney (Try to get close to the subject's face, but doesn't have to be perfect.)
  • Animate the video in Runway or Pika Labs
  • Create a voice in Elevenlabs
  • Sync the Lips in Wav2Lip
  • Upres Using Topaz Video AI with the Iris Model (Designed for Faces)
  • Faceswap Using Akool
